Upadhyaya Shri '''Guptisagarji''' is a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' who currently has the rank of an [[Upadhyaya]]. Born in 1957, he took ailak diksha under [[Acharya Vidyasagar]] ji in 1980, Muni diksha in 1982 also under Acharya Vidyasagar. He was initiated an Upadhyaya by Acharya Vidyanand ji in 1991. He is the inspiration behind Gupti Dham Jain Mandir, [[Ganaur]], [[Sonipat]].<ref>[http://hindi.webdunia.com/article/religion-news/%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE-%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0-%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82-%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A0%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B5-%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%80-%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%AE-112020100177_1.htm  गुप्तिधाम तीर्थक्षेत्र में प्रतिष्ठा महोत्सव की धूम, अहिंसा से होगा समाज का कल्याण, WebDunia, Feb 1, 2012 ]</ref>

==Biography==
He officiated over the Mahamastakabhishek of Bhagwan Adinath at [[Bawangaja]] during Jan 26 - Feb 10, 2008.<ref>[http://www.djsna.com/contentmain.aspx?id=NY00008   Mahamastakabhishek of Bhagwan Adinath at [[Bawangaja]] & DJSNA Teerth Yaatra,  Jan 26 - Feb 10, 2008]</ref>
He became the first Digambar Jain monk to visit Shimla, where he stayed at the 125 year old jain temple.<ref>प्राचीन दिगम्बर जैन मंदिर, आई. एम. जैन, सन्मतिवाणी २५ नवम्बर २०१४</ref>

Guptisagar is a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' who has got 30 publications and a [[Guinness World Record]] in his name for having inspired a dental exam involving 5,415 children at the same time.<ref>{{citation |title=एक संत का अनूठा बाल स्वच्छता अभियान! |url=http://hindi.webdunia.com/national-hindi-news/jain-muni-gupti-sagar-ji-114111400079_1.html |work=Webduniya|date=15 November 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Panchkula to have tallest Jain idol in world |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Panchkula-to-have-tallest-Jain-idol-in-world/articleshow/7623757.cms |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=4 March 2011 }}</ref>

