{{Infobox person |name=Yaacov Liberman |birth_date=1923 |birth_place=[[Harbin]] |residence=[[Shanghai]] |occupation=[[Zionism|Zionist]] politician and author }} '''Yaacov (Yana) Liberman''' (born 1923) is a [[Zionism|Zionist]] politician and author.
Liberman was born in [[Harbin]], China into a wealthy Russian Jewish family, to Semyon Liberman from [[Sevastopol]] and Gisia Zuboreva from [[Nikolayevsk-on-Amur]].<ref name="shtetlniks" /> He was a Zionist leader in [[Shanghai]]<ref name="oakton1" /> and wrote two books: ''My China: Jewish Life in the Orient: 1900–1950'' and ''Tears of Zion: Divided We Stand''.
